# Reactive (UniRx)

Package: vendored `Assets/Plugins/UniRx/` (trimmed, no uGUI). UI bindings: `Game.UI/Runtime/Extensions/UniRx/`.

## Disposal

- UI: **`UIBindingScope.Add(IDisposable)`** — required for all UITK bindings
- Gameplay MonoBehaviour: `.AddTo(this)` or `CompositeDisposable` in `OnDestroy`
- ViewModels: dispose `ReactiveProperty` / `ReactiveCommand` when screen is destroyed if not reused

## UI bindings (UI Toolkit only)

```csharp
using UniRx;
using UnityEngine.UIElements;

titleLabel.SubscribeToText(viewModel.Title);
startButton.BindTo(viewModel.StartCommand);
panel.OnPointerEnterAsObservable().Subscribe(...).AddTo(scope); // scope via UIBindingScope.Add
```

**Forbidden:** `UnityEngine.UI.*`, vendored uGUI UniRx extensions (removed from plugin).

## Observable vs EventChannel

| Use | When |
|-----|------|
| `ReactiveProperty` / `Observable` | ViewModels, streams, timers, UI binding |
| ScriptableObject EventChannel | Cross-scene broadcast, designer-authored events (when added) |

## MainThreadDispatcher

Created automatically at runtime on first UniRx scheduler use. No scene prefab required for bootstrap.

## Future migration

UniRx is legacy (2019). For new projects considering **R3** — migration is a separate effort; template standard is UniRx + UITK bridge.
